# JavaScript/TypeScript SDK Rules

## Folder Structure

The `/javascript` directory should be organized as follows:

```
javascript/
├── src/                 # JavaScript/TypeScript source code
├── tests/               # JavaScript test files (or __tests__/)
├── package.json         # Node.js package manifest
└── tsconfig.json        # TypeScript configuration (if using TypeScript)
```

## Coding Standards

- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for classes and types
- Prefer TypeScript for type safety
- Follow ESLint/Prettier configuration
- Use modern ES6+ features (async/await, destructuring, etc.)
- Export functions and classes explicitly

## TypeScript Guidelines

- Use TypeScript for all new code
- Define interfaces for API responses
- Use strict type checking
- Avoid `any` type - use `unknown` when type is truly unknown
- Provide type definitions in `.d.ts` files if needed

## Package Structure

- Organize code into logical modules
- Keep entry point clear and simple
- Use barrel exports (`index.ts`) for public API

## Testing

- Write unit tests for all public APIs
- Use Jest, Mocha, or similar testing framework
- Keep test files in `tests/` or `__tests__/` directory
- Name test files with `.test.ts` or `.spec.ts` suffix

## Dependencies

- Manage dependencies in `package.json`
- Use exact versions or version ranges appropriately
- Keep dependencies up to date and secure
